title: Shmorby
description: The Bears get a Shmorby home assistant device and become lazy couch potatoes.

title: My Clique
description: Chloe, a child prodigy, finds it difficult to connect with her much older classmates. The Bears take her under their wing and show her how to make great college friends.

title: Raincloud Chill Music Video
description: Bears just being bears written Brad Breeck and Daniel Chong.

title: Tunnels
description: The Bears discover a network of tunnels underneath the cave. Are they prepared to discover where they lead to and who dug them?

title: Sandcastle
description: The Baby Bears build a giant sandcastle. But when some kids declare war on the Bears, they must fight to defend their new home.

title: We Bare Bears The Movie
description: When Grizz, Panda, and Ice Bear catch the attention of the Department of Wildlife Control, their world turns upside down. The Bears are left with no choice but to go on the run.

title: The Demon
description: Chloe and Ice Bear accidentally lose Chloe's prized hoodie to the ferocious dog next store. They go on a mission to get it back.

title: Dreamium
description: Panda uses a relaxation app to help him get to sleep. But the the app's different sounds do more harm than good!

title: Our Stuff
description: After the bears play a little pickup basketball (they're very bad), they go back to grab their stuff by the side of the court only to find it's been stolen!  The Bears race across town trying to track down their stuff and end up cracking a giant case in the process.

title: Panda's Profile Pic
description: Panda frets over not having a good photo of himself to send to a girl online. Luckily, his brothers offer their photo editing skills to help.

title: The Fair
description: The Baby Bears make a deal with a carnival worker to be prizes for a game of ball toss.

title: Bear Cleaning
description: Ice Bear vacuums the cave and accidentally rips out a patch of Grizz's fur. He tries to fix Grizz's bald spot before he notices.

title: Spa Day
description: The Bears have a relaxing day at the spa. Grizz tries to get everything the spa has to offer. Panda gets trapped in the steam room with an old man. And Ice Bear plays ping pong.

title: Grizzly: Ultimate Hero Champion
description: Grizz records his audition tape for his favorite athletic game show.

title: The Cave
description: The Bears try to get rid of a bat in their cave.

title: Road Trip
description: Chloe and the Bears take a road trip to see a meteor shower. Ice Bear, the only one licensed to drive, is put in charge, which becomes harder than he thought.

title: I Think We Gonna Be Chillin' Music Video
description: Chillin' with a burrito written Brad Breeck and Daniel Chong.

title: Teacher's Pet
description: The Baby Bears escape their hectic lives by attending school.

title: If Only That Day Was Today Music Video
description: Baby bears reminisce written Brad Breeck and Daniel Chong.

title: Ramen
description: The Baby Bears help a struggling ramen chef perfect her ramen and save her shop.

title: Goodnight Ice Bear
description: Ice Bear tries to fall asleep but the door to his fridge won't close. He tries to come up with a fix for it in any manner possible, no matter how elaborate.

title: The Mall
description: The Bears go the mall and encounter their human counterparts.

title: Bear Stack
description: The Bears travel to the video game store to buy the last copy of a coveted new game. They encounter video game-like obstacles along the way.

title: Frozen Ice
description: Grizz and Panda find Ice Bear frozen in a block of ice and attempt to save him.

title: Charlie's Opus
description: Charlie plays some abandoned instruments in the woods. But when other animals seem interested in the music, Charlie switches from player to conductor.

title: Occupy Bears
description: When the city plans to destroy the Bears' cave in order to make way for a new cell phone tower, Grizz and Panda must find evidence from their past that proves they have rights to their land. And in case that fails, Ice Bear protests and tries to sabotage the construction crew.

title: The Gym
description: The Bears go to the gym and get quite the work out.

title: Nom Nom vs. Hamster
description: Nom Nom is forced to share the spotlight on his new video with an uncooperative hamster.

title: Cooking with Ice Bear
description: Ice Bear has a Korean-style cooking show and teaches the audience how to cook authentic Korean dishes.

title: Potty Time
description: The Baby Bears search for people to adopt them is disrupted by Panda's need to find a bathroom.

title: Panda's Dream
description: Panda gets cut in line while waiting to buy a video game and fantasizes about ways of heroically standing up for himself.

title: Log Ride
description: The Bears become obsessed with taking the perfect "action shot" picture on a log ride at an amusement park. They go on the ride over and over again until they've got the best shot.

title: Primal
description: Have the Bears lost their survival instincts by living in the modern world? Grizz wants to know so he purposefully gets the Bears lost in the deep forest.

title: Assembly Required
description: The Bears have trouble assembling some recently purchased furniture.
